  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Harjinder Singh versus The State of Punjab & Anr. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_6_168_179','2025INSC634'); ><font size='4'> <strong>HARJINDER SINGH<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>THE STATE OF PUNJAB & ANR. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 6 S.C.R. 168</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 634</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010001852025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : VIKRAM NATH<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, K.V. VISWANATHAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether the evidence led, in the instant case, justified the Trial Court&rsquo;s exercise of power u/s.319 CrPC to summon respondent no. 2, and whether the High Court was right in setting that order aside at the threshold. Headnotes&dagger; Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 attack was allegedly committed upon victim-deceased &ndash; On 10.05.2016, respondent no.2 along with other persons stopped his car near victim and taunted him stating that he and his family should die of shame for not having taken action against the acid-attack assailants &ndash; Victim returned<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 05-05-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 2477/2024</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_6_168_179','2025INSC634','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='c